gomodel:SYNGO_4656  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Fig. 6 Immunoperoxidase electron microscopy of p140Cap showed localization to presynapse and postsynapse.\n\n\"However, it should be noted that p140Cap was enriched at the pre-synapse and post-synapse in approximately 10% and 80% of synapses analyzed, respectively (data not shown). In the remaining, approximately 10% of the synapses, p140Cap was localized at both pre- and post-synaptic sides (data not shown).\". Experimental description: \"Fig. 5 Localization of p140Cap in primary cultured rat hippocampal neurons\"\n\nUsing glutathione S-transferase (GST)-Cap-C expressed in Eschechia coli as an antigen, a rabbit polyclonal antibody (anti-Cap-C) was generated and affinity-purified on a column to which the antigen\nhad been conjugated.\nMonoclonal anti-synaptophysin antibody was from Progen (Heidelberg, Germany)." ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-4973-5732" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" ;
        dc:date           "2022-05-09" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_4656" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

